What is Footprinting? (Passive vs. Active)
Footprinting is the process of gathering information about a target system, network or organization to identify potential vulnerabilities before launching an attack.
It's the first step in ehtical hacking, where hackers collect as much data as possible.

**Passive recon** = collecting information without directly interacting with the target system.
You stay “invisible” — the target doesn’t know you’re gathering data.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Tools used in passive recon**

🧠 OSINT & Intelligence Gathering
Shodan → “Google for hackers” (find exposed devices, ports, services)
Maltego → Visual link analysis (domains, emails, people, IPs)
theHarvester → Emails, domains, subdomains from public sources
Recon-ng → Full OSINT framework (like Metasploit for recon)

🌐 Domain & DNS Recon
Amass → Subdomain enumeration (very powerful)
Subfinder → Fast passive subdomain discovery
DNSdumpster / crt.sh → Certificate + DNS data
WHOIS, nslookup, dig → Basic but essential tools

📡 Internet-wide Search Engines
Netlas → Maps internet infrastructure (IPs, ports, services)
Censys → Similar to Shodan, more research-focused

📊 Passive Network Analysis
Wireshark → Analyze captured traffic without injecting packets

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**🔴 Active Reconnaissance** = direct interaction with the target system to gather information.
⚡ Active Reconnaissance Tools (Direct Interaction)

👉 Sends packets → higher risk of detection but more accurate

🔎 Network Scanning & Enumeration
Nmap → 🔥 Most important tool
Port scanning
OS detection
Service/version detection
Masscan → Ultra-fast port scanner (internet-scale)
RustScan → Faster wrapper for Nmap

🔌 Connection & Banner Grabbing
Netcat (nc) → “Swiss army knife” for networking
Telnet → Manual service interaction
Hping3 → Custom packet crafting & scanning

🧪 Vulnerability Scanning
OpenVAS → Open-source vulnerability scanner
Nessus → Industry-standard vulnerability scanner

🌍 Web Recon & Scanning
Dirb / Gobuster / FFUF → Directory brute forcing
Nikto → Web server vulnerability scanning
Burp Suite (active scan) → Web app recon & testing

🌐 DNS & Subdomain (Active)
Fierce → DNS enumeration (can be active)

